{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, there are organisms, including human beings, who pursue their goals typically relatively independently of a specification from the outside.",
    "A single-cell organism, once constituted, has an inherent drive to maintain itself: to keep the matter of which it consists organized in a certain manner, to maintain a difference between itself and its environment, to repair itself, etc.",
    "In this sense, it autonomously strives to maintain its existence.",
    "In the following, I briefly introduce the core Kantian concepts for this dichotomy: autonomy, mechanism, and organism.",
    "Autonomy In its literal meaning, autonomy means self-legislating, or self-regulating."
  ]
}